SIMPLE: trichite
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trichite
<hw>Trich"ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, <?/,
hair.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A kind of crystallite resembling a
bunch of hairs, common in obsidian. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Crystallite</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A delicate, hairlike siliceous
spicule, found in certain sponges.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Trichite sheaf</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>one of
the small sheaflike fascicles of slender setae characteristic of certain
sponges. See <xex>Illust.</xex> under <er>Spicule</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trichiuriform</ent>⟦br⟧
